main event: A person reported seeing a white object with changing colors over Westerville, Ohio on May 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, star-like object in the sky that was round, comparable to a ball.
The object was observed for about 10 minutes behind some trees.
The witness estimated the object was about 1/2 mile away and moving at an estimated speed of 1,500 mph.
There were multiple civilian aircraft in the area at the time, which could have been responsible for the sighting.
The witness reported the object suddenly went behind a cloud and disappeared from view.
sighted object: a bright, round object in the sky with changing colors
